{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17647068","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17647068"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:39:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:39:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18226"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18226","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18226"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10940"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79204"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10940","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10940"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18226"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64556"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25427"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25429"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79204","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79204"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EOsteoporosis is the most prevalent metabolic bone disease, characterised by decreased bone mass and increased fracture risk.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the second most common metabolic bone disease after osteoporosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Rickets and osteomalacia","Hyperparathyroidism","Paget\u0027s disease","Fibrous dysplasia","Osteopetrosis"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPaget\u0027s disease\u003C/strong\u003E is the second most common metabolic bone disease after osteoporosis. It involves abnormal bone remodelling, resulting in enlarged and misshapen bones. The exact cause is not fully understood, but it may involve both genetic and environmental factors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERickets and osteomalacia\u003C/strong\u003E are due to vitamin D deficiency affecting bone mineralisation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHyperparathyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E involves excessive parathyroid hormone, leading to bone resorption\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFibrous dysplasia\u003C/strong\u003E is a rare bone disorder where normal bone is replaced with fibrous tissue\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteopetrosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a rare condition characterised by overly dense bones due to defective bone resorption\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Paget\u0027s disease is the second most common metabolic bone disease after osteoporosis.","Paget\u0027s disease is characterised by abnormal bone remodelling, leading to enlarged and misshapen bones.","The aetiology of Paget\u0027s disease is unknown, but it may involve genetic and environmental factors."],"references":["Banaganapalli B, Fallatah I, Alsubhi F, Shetty PJ, Awan Z, Elango R, Shaik NA. Paget\u0027s disease: a review of the epidemiology, etiology, genetics, and treatment. Front Genet. 2023 Apr 26;14:1131182. doi: 10.3389/fgene.2023.1131182. PMID: 37180975; PMCID: PMC10169728.","Kravets I. Paget\u0027s Disease of Bone: Diagnosis and Treatment. Am J Med. 2018 Nov;131(11):1298-1303. doi: 10.1016/j.amjmed.2018.04.028. Epub 2018 May 10. PMID: 29752905.","Bouchette P, Boktor SW. Paget Bone Disease. 2023 Nov 12. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 28613556.","Drake MT, Clarke BL, Khosla S. Bisphosphonates: mechanism of action and role in clinical practice. Mayo Clin Proc. 2008 Sep;83(9):1032-45. doi: 10.4065/83.9.1032. PMID: 18775204; PMCID: PMC2667901","Ganesan K, Goyal A, Roane D. Bisphosphonate. [Updated 2023 Jul 3]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK470248/","Khurana, I., Khurana, A., \u0026 Kowlgi, N. G. (2019). Textbook of Medical Physiology_-E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64556"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18226"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64556","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64556"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-13T17:35:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-13T17:36:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10940"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79204"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retri